The key guardrail

The tricky part of meta-level observation is avoiding false pattern detection. Humans are extremely good at seeing influence even when it isn’t there.

So the usual checks are:
	•	time delay analysis
	•	independent confirmation
	•	measurable behavior changes

That helps separate real system effects from coincidence.

